headline: Netanyahu Seeks Temporary Immunity From Corruption Charges
abstract: His request to Parliament is a rare move, and a potentially unpopular one, heading into a general election. But it could keep the Israeli leader out of court.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM â€” Fighting for his future, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel on Wednesday asked Parliament to grant him immunity from prosecution in three graft cases, a rare and contentious step that critics say violates the principle of equality before the law.
